OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FGenerally dry to start, though
OL,6,Fthere could be some isolated showers
OL,7,Falong the coast in the early morning.
OL,8,FGood spells of sunshine through the
OL,9,Fmorning, though cloud may increase in
OL,10,Fthe afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA band of rain and low cloud
OL,13,Fmoving in during the evening and
OL,14,Fcontinuing overnight. Chilly, with
OL,15,Ffrost possible in rural parts.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FCloudy with spells of rain and
OL,18,Fstrong winds for the early morning.
OL,19,FThis generally clearing through the
OL,20,Fmorning, though showers are expected
OL,21,Fto develop in the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
